comment: Global offset is -1.4 to compensate glass-supported homing procedure.  MSCs (donor mix) in GelMA (T1) and HUVECs in HAMA (T2). Vol. T1: 600 µL (layer 1), + 600 µL (layer 3). Vol. T2: 600 µL (layer 2). Washing channels: dipping, then rinsing 3x1 mL warm DPBS with pipette, removing excess liquid with KimWipe (touching channels) Only 2 perfect prints with complete channels; 2 prints have incomplete channels, and channels of 2 prints barely there All prints seem to be too thick --> difficult to roll, and had slight overcuring Rolling of 3 prints, glueing with T1-220831MF in PD Pipette, then irradiation in UV chamber for 1 min. rolling was easier when prints were quite dried out All collected in separate 24-ULA-wells with 0.5 mL 2x Hase in ECGM2 +P/S

Global offset is -1.4 to compensate glass-supported homing procedure.   Remaining ink from previous print run. T2 + 400 µL Washing channels: dipping, then rinsing 3x1 mL warm DPBS with pipette, removing excess liquid with KimWipe (touching channels).  Prints had some airbubbles, also in first layer. Channels of three prints complete, some channels of other 3 prints were partly destroyed by bubbles. Last layer did not attach to prints but to printing film- not enough ink to print again. Prints gathered without "lid". Washed in DPBS, then 3 rolled and all collected in separate 24-ULA-wells with 0.5 mL 2x Hase in ECGM2 +P/S.
